  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic package carries a factor-decision inconsistency: the overall decision is Accepted yet several credibility factors are recorded without requiredLevel or achievedLevel, leaving the acceptance unsupported by structured factor evidence.",
